summary:
Hi, my name is Andreas and I am currently a master's student in Geopolitics & Connectivity in University of Groningen. 
.
For me, International Relations studies is a diversity taught. It consist of many perspectives from a variety of people. Different backgrounds, different perspectives, different actors, and different areas could be game-changer in every aspect. Therefore, I have the interest about International Relations and Affairs field. At a first glance, I am passionate in most of the I.R topics and subjects. However, I put more interest on Transnational Crime, International Politics & Security, Geopolitical Issue, and South Pacific Region. 
.
I am always eager to discover it and think about the possible solution or way out in those topics. Sometimes, I write paper research on the selected topic and discuss with other researcher and academician on national and international student conferences. I got new inside from it and made a new connection worldwide.

awards: [{'title': '5 Best Paper in Conference des etudiant.e.s indonesien.ne.s en France', 'description': 'Conference des etudiant.e.s indonesien.ne.s en France is one of work programme from Indonesia Student Association in France, supported by the Embassy of Indonesia in France. In this competition, I proposed a paper with the title " Energy Transition based on Cultural Aspect in The Global South: A Study Case in Indonesia" Moreover, from more than 100 papers, my journal selected to be presented in the embassy received a good feedback from the board of jury.', 'issuer': 'The Embassy of Indonesia in Paris, France', 'date': {'month': 11, 'day': None, 'year': 2022}}, {'title': 'University of Groningen Orange Tulip Scholarship - Faculty of Arts Talent Grant 2022-2023 Awardee', 'description': "Overall, the Orange Tulip Scholarship (OTS) Talent Grant offers a contribution towards the costs of study at the University of Groningen, to be paid in monthly installments. The grant is awarded for the duration of the Master’s degree programme in the Faculty of Art. (12 months / 18 monts or 24 monts, depending on the duration of the study progamme). Two grants per country (India, Indonesia, Russia) are available for the year 2022-2023. Furthermore, This scholarship is a part of cooperation between Nuffic Neso (non-profit organization which is funded by the Nederland's government) and Faculty of Art University of Groningen. Moreover, a selection committee reviewed the scholarship applications and students are selected on the basis of academic merit.", 'issuer': 'University of Groningen', 'date': {'month': 5, 'day': None, 'year': 2022}}, {'title': 'Speaker for Online Seminar "Getting Chance to Have International Experience | 26 September 2020 Getting Chance to Have International Experience"', 'description': 'Overall, I was designated to be a speaker for this online event regarding my international experience and study abroad. The event was attended by more than 50 young Indonesia student and scholars. In addition, the event was managed by house of ilmu Indonesia, an online educational platform to gain information and train our capability and skills regarding study abroad, self development, public speaking etc. More description about this event could be found in this link.  \n\nhttps://www.seminarhunters.com/2020/09/getting-chance-to-have-international.html', 'issuer': 'House of Ilmu Indonesia', 'date': {'month': 9, 'day': None, 'year': 2020}}, {'title': 'Best Paper of ASEAN Youth Confrence 2019 in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia', 'description': 'First and foremost, I gained this award after I presented my research paper on the Conference for ASEAN Youth Conference in 2019. Furthermore, the conference was an international student conference and be attended by international scholars mainly for Southeast Asia Region. It was held in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia. In addition, my research paper is about "The Cambridge Analytica Scandal and The General Data Protection (GDPR): A Lesson for ASEAN" (the document is available in the publication section). In addition, my research paper received positive feedbacks from other scholars.', 'issuer': 'PPI Malaysia', 'date': {'month': 10, 'day': None, 'year': 2019}}, {'title': '1st Place in French Presentation Competition "La Francofête" UNNES Central java Region ', 'description': 'La Francofête is a french festival in Semarang that be held by Universitas Negeri Semarang. Overall, It showed most of the french culture, music, and traditional cuisine. Beside the festival, the committee was also held a language competition for senior high school with a variety of category. I was selected as a delegate from my High School for Presentation Competition with my friend. Moreovore, I presented Semarang historical places to be visited for foreign tourist with French language. In addition, the presentation competition is a central java regional competition which was followed by students from Central Java province. In summary, my presentation received a positive feedback from the committee and I won the1st place for my performance with a additional trophy and certificate.', 'issuer': 'Universitas Negeri Semarang ', 'date': {'month': 5, 'day': None, 'year': 2016}}]

volunteer_experiences:
[{'date': {'start': {'month': 6, 'day': None, 'year': 2018}, 'end': {'month': 8, 'day': None, 'year': 2018}}, 'role': 'Global Volunteer ', 'company': {'id': None, 'name': 'AIESEC in Ahmedabad', 'logo': 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/C4E0BAQF0Sk62NB5qDw/company-logo_400_400/0/1519876145801?e=1700697600&v=beta&t=zmhLp_fzQzwoeMSpRFK3QZp1JdrhVAaGHldGnu_Wq8o', 'url': 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/aiesecahmedabad/'}, 'cause': 'EDUCATION', 'description': 'I am one of the Global Volunteer in Namaste 6.0/ Worldview Project (based on SDG's no. 4), hosted by Pandit Deendayal Petroleum University (PDPU) . We taught in a elementary school with the other international volunteers from around the world. With other volunteers who come from many countries, we taught in "The New Little Flower Higher Secondary School".  We also learn about Indian Culture and we had many cultural understanding between the volunteers and locals. 
 
The main activities in this project were :
